text: The most famous Parisian cabaret the Moulin Rouge is celebrating its anniversary of 130 years. The milestone has been marked by a 10 minute colourful light and sound show, retracing the venue's rich history. Artists from the company also performed the famous Can Can dance in the national tricolours of red, white and blue. The cabaret, famous for its high-kicking dancers and ostrich feather costumes first opened doors in 1889, attracting more than 600,000 tourists annually from across the world. Image: AP
